@startuml fig-S04-e2-message-flow
skinparam backgroundColor white
skinparam defaultFontName Arial
skinparam defaultFontSize 11
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center

title S04 — E2 Primary Path: Allowed and Blocked Proxy Requests

participant "tester" as C #FFE0B2
participant "http_proxy\n:3128" as P #E1BEE7
participant "origin_server\n:8080" as O #C8E6C9

== ALLOWED REQUEST ==
C -> P : GET http://origin:8080/allowed.html HTTP/1.1
P -> O : SYN (proxy → origin)
O --> P : SYN-ACK
P -> O : GET /allowed.html HTTP/1.1\nHost: origin
O -[#43A047]-> P : HTTP/1.1 200 OK\n(body)
P -[#43A047]-> C : HTTP/1.1 200 OK\n(forwarded body)

note right of P : Log: 200 | origin:8080/allowed.html | 1.2ms

== BLOCKED REQUEST ==
C -> P : GET http://origin:8080/blocked.html HTTP/1.1
P -[#E53935]-> C : HTTP/1.1 403 Forbidden\n(blacklist match)

note right of P #FFCDD2 : Log: 403 | BLOCKED | rule: URL blacklist

== CONNECT (HTTPS TUNNEL — E3) ==
C -> P : CONNECT secure.example:443 HTTP/1.1
P -[#1565C0]-> C : HTTP/1.1 200 Connection Established
C <-> P : (opaque TLS tunnel)

legend right
  PCAP shows two hops: client–proxy, proxy–origin
  Blocked requests never reach origin
  CONNECT creates a bidirectional tunnel
  Validates R1–R4 in S04.json
endlegend
@enduml
